00:51:12,116 --> 00:51:14,931
"Behind books, third shelf,

1017
00:51:14,997 --> 00:51:17,681
secretary, Doctor 'S'."

1018
00:51:17,747 --> 00:51:20,351
Well, outside of the fact that Davidson
hid the Bank of England plates

1019
00:51:20,417 --> 00:51:21,772
somewhere in London, Mr. Holmes,

1020
00:51:21,838 --> 00:51:23,812
I don't see that we've progressed at all.

1021
00:51:23,878 --> 00:51:29,322
Allow me to point out to you,
sir, the key words Doctor 'S'.

1022
00:51:29,388 --> 00:51:32,453
It looks as if the plates were
hidden in the house of a doctor.

1023
00:51:32,519 --> 00:51:34,913
Whether the 'S' stands for
his first or last initial

1024
00:51:34,979 --> 00:51:37,834
remains to be determined by
a process of elimination.

1025
00:51:37,900 --> 00:51:40,084
Well, there must be ten
thousand doctors in London

1026
00:51:40,150 --> 00:51:42,754
with 'S' for a first or last initial.

1027
00:51:42,820 --> 00:51:44,874
Precisely and every one of them

1028
00:51:44,940 --> 00:51:46,545
will have to be questioned in person.

1029
00:51:46,611 --> 00:51:49,175
That's why I say this is
a task for Scotland Yard.

1030
00:51:49,241 --> 00:51:51,055
It's a task all right

1031
00:51:51,121 --> 00:51:54,346
but Scotland Yard has searched worse
haystacks and found a needle.

1032
00:51:54,412 --> 00:51:56,346
Well, for the time being

1033
00:51:56,412 --> 00:51:58,816
I'll leave the matter in
your hands, gentlemen.

1034
00:51:58,882 --> 00:52:03,447
We'll call you if and when we get a
lead on our mysterious Doctor S.

1035
00:52:03,513 --> 00:52:04,607
Thank you.

1036
00:52:04,673 --> 00:52:05,737
In the meantime, I intend to follow up

1037
00:52:05,803 --> 00:52:08,233
a little clue concerning a cigarette.

1038
00:52:14,724 --> 00:52:17,288
You are certain of the
identification of the tobacco?

1039
00:52:17,354 --> 00:52:18,538
Absolutely.

1040
00:52:18,604 --> 00:52:20,169
I have made up this special blend

1041
00:52:20,235 --> 00:52:22,629
for only three customers.

1042
00:52:22,695 --> 00:52:25,179
It is almost pure Egyptian

1043
00:52:25,245 --> 00:52:29,140
with a mixture of Latakia for added body

1044
00:52:29,206 --> 00:52:31,310
and a pinch of Perique,

1045
00:52:31,376 --> 00:52:33,730
merely a whisper as one might say

1046
00:52:33,796 --> 00:52:35,981
- for elusive fragrance.
- Yes Yes,

1047
00:52:36,047 --> 00:52:38,441
and the three customers?

1048
00:52:38,507 --> 00:52:41,901
Major Wilson in Bombay, India.

1049
00:52:41,967 --> 00:52:45,652
Mrs. Catherine Lemington
Smith in Ireland.

1050
00:52:45,718 --> 00:52:47,362
Yes and the third?

1051
00:52:47,428 --> 00:52:51,493
Mrs. Hilda Courtney of Park
Mansions, Briarstone Square.

1052
00:52:51,559 --> 00:52:53,703
Thank you. Thank you very much.
You've been most helpful.

1053
00:52:53,769 --> 00:52:56,359
It is a pleasure to of
been service, Mr. Holmes.

1054
00:53:06,540 --> 00:53:07,844
Yes?

1055
00:53:07,911 --> 00:53:09,095
Mrs. Courtney?

1056
00:53:09,161 --> 00:53:10,095
Yes.

1057
00:53:10,161 --> 00:53:12,015
My name is Sherlock Holmes.

1058
00:53:12,081 --> 00:53:14,645
- Do come in.
- Thank you.

1059
00:53:14,711 --> 00:53:17,282
I've heard of you,
of course, Mr. Holmes.

1060
00:53:18,802 --> 00:53:21,866
I believe we have a mutual
friend in Sir Edward Brookdale.

1061
00:53:21,932 --> 00:53:23,786
He's spoken to me of you quite often.

1062
00:53:23,852 --> 00:53:25,363
Indeed.

1063
00:53:27,603 --> 00:53:31,077
And to what good fortune
am I indebted for this visit?

1064
00:53:31,143 --> 00:53:32,958
I think you know, Mrs. Courtney.

1065
00:53:33,024 --> 00:53:37,218
Well, I did get a summons
for speeding last week

1066
00:53:37,284 --> 00:53:40,428
but outside of that I don't think
I'm of any interest to the police.

1067
00:53:40,494 --> 00:53:41,929
Oh, come now, Mrs. Courtney,

1068
00:53:41,995 --> 00:53:44,389
you seemed to forget that
you and I have met before.

1069
00:53:44,455 --> 00:53:46,309
I'm sorry,

1070
00:53:46,375 --> 00:53:48,940
I'm sure I would have remembered
meeting the great Sherlock Holmes.

1071
00:53:49,006 --> 00:53:51,600
- Please sit down.
- Thank you.

1072
00:53:51,666 --> 00:53:53,400
You say we met before?

1073
00:53:53,466 --> 00:53:55,190
Yes.

1074
00:53:55,256 --> 00:53:59,901
At the home of Mr. & Mrs.
Kilgour, 143 B Hampton Road.

1075
00:53:59,967 --> 00:54:01,531
Kilgour?

1076
00:54:01,597 --> 00:54:04,991
I don't think I know anyone of that name.

1077
00:54:05,057 --> 00:54:07,252
Well, I didn't say you knew them,

1078
00:54:07,318 --> 00:54:10,622
as a matter of fact, you called
on them when they were out.

1079
00:54:10,688 --> 00:54:13,252
Why I don't understand,
Mr. Holmes.

1080
00:54:13,318 --> 00:54:14,753
Really?

1081
00:54:14,819 --> 00:54:16,843
You were dressed rather differently.

1082
00:54:16,909 --> 00:54:18,843
Indeed.

1083
00:54:18,909 --> 00:54:20,789
Cigarette?

1084
00:54:21,950 --> 00:54:22,750
Thank you.

1085
00:54:39,602 --> 00:54:42,246
You know Mrs. Courtney,
people generally forget,

1086
00:54:42,312 --> 00:54:44,826
you know assuming your disguise,

1087
00:54:44,892 --> 00:54:46,497
that the shape of the ear

1088
00:54:46,563 --> 00:54:48,587
is almost an infallible
means of recognition

1089
00:54:48,653 --> 00:54:50,797
and identification to the trained eye.

1090
00:54:50,863 --> 00:54:52,877
Evidently you've mistaken
me for someone else.

1091
00:54:52,943 --> 00:54:54,047
Oh no, not at all,

1092
00:54:54,113 --> 00:54:57,178
though naturally I expected your denial

1093
00:54:57,244 --> 00:55:00,268
but when you paid your visit
to my rooms at Baker Street

1094
00:55:00,334 --> 00:55:02,689
you carelessly left behind

1095
00:55:02,755 --> 00:55:05,859
an another identification.

1096
00:55:05,925 --> 00:55:09,729
They're identical aren't they?

1097
00:55:09,795 --> 00:55:12,030
Yes, I must admit they are.

1098
00:55:12,096 --> 00:55:14,410
You see Mr. Holmes to
catch one as clever as you

1099
00:55:14,476 --> 00:55:16,990
I had to use a very special lure.

1100
00:55:17,056 --> 00:55:19,951
I knew you'd be unable to
resist the bait of my cigarette

1101
00:55:20,017 --> 00:55:22,831
having read with great interest
your monograph on the ashes

1102
00:55:22,897 --> 00:55:26,171
of a hundred and forty
different varieties of tobacco.

1103
00:55:26,237 --> 00:55:31,672
I should advise you
not to move, Mr. Holmes.

1104
00:55:31,738 --> 00:55:34,682
I must congratulate you on
your ingenuity, Mrs. Courtney.

1105
00:55:34,748 --> 00:55:36,933
It was indeed a brilliantly designed trap.

1106
00:55:36,999 --> 00:55:38,603
Thank you, Mr. Holmes.

1107
00:55:38,669 --> 00:55:41,773
Praise from a master is indeed gratifying.

1108
00:55:41,839 --> 00:55:46,354
I shall always cherish the memory
of your flatter and words.

1109
00:55:46,420 --> 00:55:48,564
Memory?

1110
00:55:48,630 --> 00:55:50,404
Precisely.

1111
00:55:50,470 --> 00:55:53,325
I'm afraid these gentlemen have a
most regrettable task to perform.

1112
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:57,995
Unless, of course, you care to
turn over the missing musical box

1113
00:55:58,061 --> 00:56:02,206
with your pledge to take no
action against us in the future.

1114
00:56:02,272 --> 00:56:04,006
I'm afraid that will be impossible.

1115
00:56:04,072 --> 00:56:06,716
I thought that would
be your answer. Hamid!

1116
00:56:06,782 --> 00:56:08,297
Careful!

1117
00:56:08,363 --> 00:56:11,637
Careful, there's no need
to be unnecessarily rough

1118
00:56:11,703 --> 00:56:13,267
with our distinguished guest.

1119
00:56:13,333 --> 00:56:14,557
You realize, Mr. Holmes,

1120
00:56:14,623 --> 00:56:17,228
that your demise will not take place here,

1121
00:56:17,294 --> 00:56:20,818
the Corpus Delicti you know?

1122
00:56:20,884 --> 00:56:22,358
Well, naturally.

1123
00:56:22,424 --> 00:56:23,934
Shall we go?

1124
00:56:25,965 --> 00:56:29,319
So fearfully awkward having
a dead body lying about.

1125
00:56:29,385 --> 00:56:30,699
Don't you agree, Mr. Holmes?

1126
00:56:30,765 --> 00:56:32,119
Another dead body shouldn't
weigh too heavily

1127
00:56:32,185 --> 00:56:34,156
on your conscious,
Mrs. Courtney.

1128
00:56:43,657 --> 00:56:45,971
Do you mind if I have a cigarette?

1129
00:56:46,037 --> 00:56:48,237
Why I don't see why not.

1130
00:57:01,049 --> 00:57:03,653
Be careful, Hamid.

1131
00:57:03,719 --> 00:57:05,920
It's the brakes, they bind.

1132
00:57:08,140 --> 00:57:09,574
Thank you Colonel Cavanaugh,

1133
00:57:09,640 --> 00:57:11,290
it's very considerate of you.

1134
00:57:41,554 --> 00:57:43,318
You'll be happy to know,
Mr. Holmes,

1135
00:57:43,384 --> 00:57:46,464
that your death will be a painless one.

1136
00:57:48,145 --> 00:57:49,749
Hamid,

1137
00:57:49,815 --> 00:57:52,835
attach this to the motor of the taxi.

1138
00:57:55,406 --> 00:57:57,760
That little attachment,
my dear Mr. Holmes,

1139
00:57:57,826 --> 00:58:01,680
contains the deadly fluid
known as, monosulfide,

1140
00:58:01,746 --> 00:58:03,931
the Germans use it with gratifying results

1141
00:58:03,997 --> 00:58:07,577
in removing their undesirables.

1142
00:58:11,628 --> 00:58:13,508
Start the motor.

1143
00:58:35,320 --> 00:58:36,791
Tape his mouth.

1144
00:58:44,212 --> 00:58:48,562
Now, up with him, Hamid.

1145
00:58:57,263 --> 00:59:01,948
You find yourself like
Muhammad's coffin, Mr. Holmes,

1146
00:59:02,014 --> 00:59:07,064
suspended between heaven and Earth.

1147
00:59:10,945 --> 00:59:13,669
Plenty of fuel in the tank?

1148
00:59:13,735 --> 00:59:15,009
Good.

1149
00:59:15,075 --> 00:59:17,010
It would be too bad to
have anything go wrong

1150
00:59:17,076 --> 00:59:20,926
through so simple an oversight.

1151
01:00:29,954 --> 01:00:30,969
Good afternoon.

1152
01:00:31,035 --> 01:00:32,299
Mr. Sherlock Holmes?

1153
01:00:32,365 --> 01:00:33,969
No, I'm Doctor Watson.

1154
01:00:34,035 --> 01:00:36,309
Oh, of course, Doctor Watson.

1155
01:00:36,375 --> 01:00:37,769
How stupid of me.

1156
01:00:37,835 --> 01:00:40,560
Not at all, it's stupid of me.

1157
01:00:40,626 --> 01:00:41,770
Won't you come in?

1158
01:00:41,836 --> 01:00:44,150
Well, I really came
to see Mr. Holmes.

1159
01:00:44,216 --> 01:00:46,740
Oh I'm afraid he's out. I don't
know when he'll be back.

1160
01:00:46,806 --> 01:00:48,401
Perhaps there's something I can do.

1161
01:00:48,467 --> 01:00:49,701
Won't you sit down?

1162
01:00:49,767 --> 01:00:51,031
Thank you.

1163
01:00:51,097 --> 01:00:53,911
You know Sherlock Holmes
and I have been engaged

1164
01:00:53,977 --> 01:00:55,702
on a great many cases.

1165
01:00:55,768 --> 01:00:57,502
- Oh, really?
- Yes indeed.

1166
01:00:57,568 --> 01:00:59,372
As a matter of fact,

1167
01:00:59,438 --> 01:01:02,002
at this very moment we're involved
in one of the most baffling...

1168
01:01:02,068 --> 01:01:04,593
Well, won't you tell me your trouble.

1169
01:01:04,659 --> 01:01:05,923
I may be able to help you.

1170
01:01:05,989 --> 01:01:07,843
That's very kind of you, Doctor Watson,

1171
01:01:07,909 --> 01:01:11,263
perhaps if I wouldn't
be imposing too much...

1172
01:01:11,329 --> 01:01:12,604
Imposing?

1173
01:01:12,670 --> 01:01:15,104
Oh, it's no imposition,
no imposition at all.

1174
01:01:15,170 --> 01:01:16,724
A pleasure I assure you now.

1175
01:01:16,790 --> 01:01:18,934
- Tell me all about it Miss...
- Miss Williams.

1176
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:20,645
Mrs. Williams.

1177
01:01:20,711 --> 01:01:22,355
I live in Surrey, Doctor Watson,

1178
01:01:22,421 --> 01:01:25,075
and I've come to London
on sheer desperation.

1179
01:01:25,141 --> 01:01:26,615
My only sister has disappeared

1180
01:01:26,681 --> 01:01:28,946
and the local police seem
utterly unable to find her.

1181
01:01:29,012 --> 01:01:31,746
Well, Holmes and I solved a
case exactly like that once.

1182
01:01:31,812 --> 01:01:33,916
Very interesting as far as I remember.

1183
01:01:33,982 --> 01:01:35,956
I called it

1184
01:01:36,022 --> 01:01:38,377
"The Adventure Of The
Solitary Cyclist."

1185
01:01:38,443 --> 01:01:40,757
Oh, sorry. Now I
come to think of it,

1186
01:01:40,823 --> 01:01:43,887
it wasn't so very similar,
entirely different now.

1187
01:01:43,953 --> 01:01:45,808
I can't figure what I was saying.

1188
01:01:45,874 --> 01:01:48,138
Where were we?

1189
01:01:48,204 --> 01:01:50,518
She's only seventeen, Doctor Watson

1190
01:01:50,584 --> 01:01:52,518
and until she disappeared last Thursday

1191
01:01:52,584 --> 01:01:55,899
she seemed to be in the best of spirits.

1192
01:01:55,965 --> 01:01:58,609
Well, possibly a romantic entanglement.

1193
01:01:58,675 --> 01:02:00,529
Oh no, no, nothing of the sort.

1194
01:02:00,595 --> 01:02:03,110
She left no note, didn't even pack a bag,

1195
01:02:03,176 --> 01:02:04,700
no explanation,

1196
01:02:04,766 --> 01:02:06,240
she just started to walk to the village

1197
01:02:06,306 --> 01:02:08,450
from our house in broad daylight

1198
01:02:08,516 --> 01:02:10,581
and simply vanished from
the face of the Earth.

1199
01:02:10,647 --> 01:02:13,211
Oh there, there, there, there.

1200
01:02:13,277 --> 01:02:14,461
Might I have a glass of water?

1201
01:02:14,527 --> 01:02:16,841
Glass of water,
yes of course. Glass of...

1202
01:02:16,907 --> 01:02:18,598
I'll have one in one minute.

1203
01:02:50,152 --> 01:02:51,166
There you are, my dear.

1204
01:02:51,232 --> 01:02:53,166
Thank you, Doctor Watson.

1205
01:02:53,232 --> 01:02:54,466
Now, now you're not to cry anymore.

1206
01:02:54,532 --> 01:02:56,336
You must pull yourself together.

1207
01:02:56,402 --> 01:02:58,507
I feel much better already knowing
that you're going to help me.

1208
01:02:58,573 --> 01:03:00,177
Oh, Doctor Watson, look!

1209
01:03:00,243 --> 01:03:01,803
Good heavens!

1210
01:03:05,753 --> 01:03:08,504
Get through, get through
the fire brigade, quickly.

1211
01:03:12,214 --> 01:03:14,649
Haven't you a fire extinguisher?

1212
01:03:14,715 --> 01:03:16,915
By Jove, we have one, in the kitchen.

1213
01:03:39,328 --> 01:03:40,472
Don't you worry, Miss Williams

1214
01:03:40,538 --> 01:03:42,518
we'll have this thing out in no time.

1215
01:03:52,179 --> 01:03:54,009
Now, that's got it.

1216
01:03:57,930 --> 01:03:59,400
Let's get some air.

1217
01:04:01,270 --> 01:04:05,125
Well, you see there was no need
for the fire brigade after all.

1218
01:04:05,191 --> 01:04:07,851
I hope you weren't too
frightened, Miss Williams.

1219
01:04:10,451 --> 01:04:12,506
Oh, gone.

1220
01:04:12,572 --> 01:04:14,096
That's the trouble with women,

1221
01:04:14,162 --> 01:04:16,632
they always lose their
heads in an emergency.

1222
01:04:19,662 --> 01:04:21,043
Hello.

1223
01:04:25,383 --> 01:04:28,568
The musical box.

1224
01:04:28,634 --> 01:04:30,374
Great Scott!

1225
01:04:34,014 --> 01:04:35,344
Miss Williams!

1226
01:04:41,275 --> 01:04:42,695
Well?

1227
01:04:43,695 --> 01:04:44,880
Good.

1228
01:04:44,946 --> 01:04:45,920
And Holmes?

1229
01:04:45,986 --> 01:04:47,420
By now Mr. Holmes has no doubt

1230
01:04:47,486 --> 01:04:50,010
exchanged his violin for a harp.

1231
01:04:50,076 --> 01:04:53,337
Oh, well assuming that
heaven is his destination.

1232
01:04:55,247 --> 01:04:57,667
And now that we have
the missing musical box.

1233
01:05:08,058 --> 01:05:12,033
- Nineteenth note,
- Nineteenth note,

1234
01:05:12,099 --> 01:05:15,833
- nineteenth letter.
- Nineteenth letter.

1235
01:05:15,899 --> 01:05:17,730
"S".

1236
01:05:20,070 --> 01:05:21,924
He hasn't been there you say?

1237
01:05:21,990 --> 01:05:23,794
Holmes, where on earth
where have you been?

1238
01:05:23,860 --> 01:05:25,384
I've been trying to get you at the club,

1239
01:05:25,450 --> 01:05:27,601
at Scotland Yard, all over London.

1240
01:05:29,331 --> 01:05:31,515
You were looking for
me in the wrong places.

1241
01:05:31,581 --> 01:05:33,595
Holmes, a terrible thing's happened.

1242
01:05:33,661 --> 01:05:35,146
I've been duped.

1243
01:05:35,212 --> 01:05:36,936
That woman,

1244
01:05:37,002 --> 01:05:38,816
- she made a complete fool of me.
- Well, what do you mean?

1245
01:05:38,882 --> 01:05:41,066
Well, she came here and
let off a smoke bomb.

1246
01:05:41,132 --> 01:05:42,397
I thought the whole place was on fire

1247
01:05:42,463 --> 01:05:44,737
and my first thought was
to save the musical box.

1248
01:05:44,803 --> 01:05:46,697
No need to say anymore.

1249
01:05:46,763 --> 01:05:47,907
She has the box.

1250
01:05:47,973 --> 01:05:49,997
Yes.

1251
01:05:50,063 --> 01:05:53,618
Don't blame yourself too much, old fellow.

1252
01:05:53,684 --> 01:05:56,344
She is an extremely clever antagonist.

1253
01:05:59,195 --> 01:06:03,379
Smoke bomb you said?

1254
01:06:03,445 --> 01:06:06,349
Well, you can console
yourself with the thought

1255
01:06:06,415 --> 01:06:08,930
that your charming friend
is at least a reader of yours.

1256
01:06:08,996 --> 01:06:10,140
What do you mean?

1257
01:06:10,206 --> 01:06:12,100
If I remember correctly,

1258
01:06:12,166 --> 01:06:14,400
you wrote about my little experiment
with the smoke and the cry of fire

1259
01:06:14,466 --> 01:06:17,061
in the story you entitled
"A Scandal in Bohemia",

1260
01:06:17,127 --> 01:06:18,941
which has just appeared
in the Strand Magazine.

1261
01:06:19,007 --> 01:06:23,242
All right, all right, old boy,
don't rub it in.

1262
01:06:23,308 --> 01:06:27,952
It may cheer you up to know
that she made a fool of me too.

1263
01:06:28,018 --> 01:06:30,122
With that cigarette stub.

1264
01:06:30,188 --> 01:06:33,213
It was planted here for
one express purpose.

1265
01:06:33,279 --> 01:06:34,833
Do we have any bandaging
around this place?

1266
01:06:34,899 --> 01:06:37,423
Bandaging? What's the matter, Holmes?
You hurt?

1267
01:06:37,489 --> 01:06:39,594
Explanations will have
to wait until later,

1268
01:06:39,660 --> 01:06:41,634
at the moment we're faced with a problem,

1269
01:06:41,700 --> 01:06:43,304
which I fear, is insurmountable.

1270
01:06:43,370 --> 01:06:45,850
- Come over here, old boy, will ya?
- Right.

1271
01:06:47,330 --> 01:06:48,765
Now the opponents are in possession

1272
01:06:48,831 --> 01:06:50,435
of all three parts of the code

1273
01:06:50,501 --> 01:06:53,145
and here are we while the
Bank of England plates

1274
01:06:53,211 --> 01:06:54,605
pass into their possession.

1275
01:06:54,671 --> 01:06:56,356
Cheer up, old fellow, cheer up.

1276
01:06:56,422 --> 01:06:58,066
As Doctor Samuel Johnson once said

1277
01:06:58,132 --> 01:07:00,826
"There's no problem the
mind of man can set

1278
01:07:00,892 --> 01:07:03,086
that the mind of
man cannot solve."

1279
01:07:03,152 --> 01:07:06,257
- What's that, old fellow?
- I was quoting Doctor Samuel Johnson,

1280
01:07:06,323 --> 01:07:09,343
- he said there is no...
- Thank you, Watson, thank you.

1281
01:07:12,814 --> 01:07:14,838
Leaving the front reception room

1282
01:07:14,904 --> 01:07:16,928
we come into the main hall

1283
01:07:16,994 --> 01:07:19,968
where Doctor Johnson was in
the habit of passing through

1284
01:07:20,034 --> 01:07:22,969
to have his meager meals in
the dining room opposite.

1285
01:07:23,035 --> 01:07:25,559
In company with his friend and biographer,

1286
01:07:25,625 --> 01:07:27,849
James Bosvo.

1287
01:07:27,915 --> 01:07:29,860
We will now pass up the stairway,

1288
01:07:29,926 --> 01:07:33,070
which remains in it's natural wood finish.

1289
01:07:33,136 --> 01:07:36,150
Just as it was when the
good doctor was here.

1290
01:07:36,216 --> 01:07:37,911
The framed etching on the wall

1291
01:07:37,977 --> 01:07:40,531
is believed to have been
presented to Doctor Johnson

1292
01:07:40,597 --> 01:07:44,371
by the distinguished painter,
Sir Joshua Reynolds.

1293
01:07:44,437 --> 01:07:46,622
I've been told here that that picture

1294
01:07:46,688 --> 01:07:48,462
was given to him by Mrs. Tarrel

1295
01:07:48,528 --> 01:07:50,922
and its definitely not a Reynolds.

1296
01:07:50,988 --> 01:07:53,673
Is that important, my dear?

1297
01:07:53,739 --> 01:07:55,893
Oh, I'm sorry.

1298
01:07:55,959 --> 01:07:58,383
This way ladies and
gentlemen please, this way.

1299
01:07:58,449 --> 01:08:00,569
Move along children, move along.

1300
01:08:01,429 --> 01:08:03,064
The secretary's not on this floor.

1301
01:08:03,130 --> 01:08:04,524
Patience, Hamid.

1302
01:08:04,590 --> 01:08:06,484
- I have a feeling...
- My dear Colonel

1303
01:08:06,550 --> 01:08:10,031
with Sherlock Holmes out of
the way what could go wrong?

1304
01:08:17,681 --> 01:08:20,286
And here we have the gallant library

1305
01:08:20,352 --> 01:08:23,626
in which Doctor Johnson
wrote his famous dictionary

1306
01:08:23,692 --> 01:08:25,546
and in which you will see also

1307
01:08:25,612 --> 01:08:27,006
many of the great man's books

1308
01:08:27,073 --> 01:08:29,086
and other items of interest.

1309
01:08:29,153 --> 01:08:32,176
Step forward ladies and
gentlemen, please step forward.

1310
01:08:32,243 --> 01:08:34,428
Standing in the corner is the secretary,

1311
01:08:34,494 --> 01:08:36,768
which contains many of the original works

1312
01:08:36,834 --> 01:08:38,978
by the literary genius.

1313
01:08:39,044 --> 01:08:42,148
On this table Doctor Johnson's cat Hodge

1314
01:08:42,214 --> 01:08:44,009
used to sleep while his master worked.

1315
01:08:44,075 --> 01:08:46,831
But the strange thing
about this cat, ladies

1316
01:08:46,897 --> 01:08:49,398
and gentlemen, was its love of oysters.

1317
01:08:49,465 --> 01:08:51,910
They do say that the dear
Doctor often went hungry

1318
01:08:51,976 --> 01:08:54,950
to find the cat that delicacy.

1319
01:08:55,015 --> 01:08:56,700
What a pity.

1320
01:08:56,765 --> 01:08:58,160
Now we will visit the bedroom,

1321
01:08:58,226 --> 01:09:00,371
which is immediately below us

1322
01:09:00,437 --> 01:09:02,621
in which you will see the very bed

1323
01:09:02,687 --> 01:09:04,671
in which Doctor Johnson died.

1324
01:09:04,737 --> 01:09:06,921
What did he die of?

1325
01:09:06,987 --> 01:09:08,342
Gout.

1326
01:09:08,407 --> 01:09:10,232
Just gout.

1327
01:09:10,298 --> 01:09:11,842
This way ladies and gentlemen,

1328
01:09:11,907 --> 01:09:13,558
mind the steps please.

1329
01:09:26,430 --> 01:09:27,990
The keys.

1330
01:09:44,192 --> 01:09:45,892
Third shelf up.

1331
01:09:52,122 --> 01:09:53,593
The knife.

1332
01:09:58,834 --> 01:10:01,724
Gentlemen, the Bank of England plates.

1333
01:10:03,714 --> 01:10:05,199
Well, Mrs. Courtney,

1334
01:10:05,264 --> 01:10:07,489
so we meet again.

1335
01:10:07,555 --> 01:10:10,489
Now, I shouldn't do that if I
were you, Colonel Cavanaugh.

1336
01:10:10,555 --> 01:10:12,830
I must congratulate you,
Mr. Holmes.

1337
01:10:12,896 --> 01:10:16,670
You're far more clever than I thought.

1338
01:10:16,736 --> 01:10:18,920
Thank you, Mrs. Courtney.

1339
01:10:18,986 --> 01:10:22,050
Praise from you is indeed gratifying.

1340
01:10:22,117 --> 01:10:24,630
I shall always cherish the memory

1341
01:10:24,697 --> 01:10:26,471
of your flattering words.

1342
01:10:26,537 --> 01:10:27,931
Memory?

1343
01:10:27,996 --> 01:10:30,722
Oh, thank you.

1344
01:10:30,788 --> 01:10:34,318
And now I have a most
regrettable task to perform.

1345
01:10:38,969 --> 01:10:41,023
Holmes!

1346
01:10:41,089 --> 01:10:42,789
Coming Holmes!

1347
01:10:44,259 --> 01:10:45,654
Holmes!

1348
01:10:45,719 --> 01:10:46,664
You all right?

1349
01:10:46,730 --> 01:10:49,424
Perfectly, thank you, old fellow but
I think this gentleman on the floor

1350
01:10:49,490 --> 01:10:51,074
requires some medical attention.

1351
01:10:51,139 --> 01:10:53,334
We must see that he looks his
best, you know, when he's hanged.

1352
01:10:53,400 --> 01:10:54,911
Take them in charge.

1353
01:11:11,463 --> 01:11:14,107
A brilliant antagonist.

1354
01:11:14,173 --> 01:11:16,597
It's a pity her talents
were so misdirected.

1355
01:11:16,663 --> 01:11:18,117
Will you see that these plates

1356
01:11:18,183 --> 01:11:20,098
are returned to the Bank
of England, Inspector?

1357
01:11:20,164 --> 01:11:22,148
I still don't understand how
you solved it, Mr. Holmes.

1358
01:11:22,214 --> 01:11:24,198
It's entirely due to Doctor Watson.

1359
01:11:24,264 --> 01:11:27,459
He gave me the clue when he
mentioned Doctor Samuel Johnson.

1360
01:11:27,525 --> 01:11:29,228
Well, congratulations, Doctor.

1361
01:11:29,295 --> 01:11:30,559
Oh, thank you, Inspector.

1362
01:11:30,625 --> 01:11:34,956
I don't think I could have done it
entirely without Mr. Holmes' help you know?

